            <title>[MJAVADOC-657] The fix operation duplicates annotations on private methods that have an annotation line between the method body and the javadoc comments.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-657</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/pull/52&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/pull/52&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There be several bugs happened during my usage of maven-javadoc-plugin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now I found some time to report them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I add it in unit test(and it will fail the test now) in this pr, showing when it happens, how it will harm the codes, and what be the expected result.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now I&apos;m being looking up the sources to see if I can fix it by myself, but I think it be good to let you know about the bug before I started.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
